Israeli Stocks: Ampal, British-Israel, Delek Fuel, El Al, ICL

-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 
2011-02-13T10:43:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/israeli-stocks-ampal-british-israel-delek-fuel-el-al-icl.html
  Israel ’s TA-25 Index advanced for
the first time in four days, increasing 0.9 percent to 1,314.06
at 12:10 p.m. in Tel Aviv.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.        Ampal-American Israel  Corp. (AMPL IT) gained for the first
time in three days, climbing 4 percent to 7.957 shekels. The
company owns a 12.5 percent stake in East Mediterranean Gas Co.,
which operates a pipeline to Israel from Egypt.    British-Israel Investments Ltd . (BRTS IT) jumped the most
in more than five months, advancing 7 percent to 12.49 shekels.  Melisron Ltd . (MLSR IT) agreed on terms to acquire the real-
estate investment company. Melisron rose for the first time in
three days, increasing 2.7 percent to 90.87 shekels.       Delek The Israeli Fuel Corp. (DLKIS IT) advanced for the
first time in three days, adding 2 percent to 124.40 shekels.
The owner of gas stations in Israel plans to invest “hundreds
of millions of shekels” over the next five years to build and
develop retail centers.        El Al Israel Airlines  Ltd. (ELAL IT) rose 2.1 percent to
1.493 shekels, poised for the highest close since Jan. 27. The
country’s national carrier reached a compromise agreement with
Israel’s Income Tax Authority regarding discounted plane tickets
given to employees.    Israel Chemicals Ltd . (ICL IT) increased for the first time
in three days, gaining 1.2 percent to 62.51 shekels. The company
that extracts minerals from the Dead Sea to make fertilizer
signed agreements to supply Chinese clients with 500,000 tons of
potash in the first half of 2011.       Modiin Energy LP (MDINL IT) gained the most in a week,
climbing 2.3 percent to 0.044 shekel. The energy exploration
company said it’s in preliminary talks with Avner Oil
Exploration LP (AVNRL IT) and Delek Drilling LP (DEDRL) to
purchase rights to two licenses. Avner and Delek Drilling rose
0.2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
